went fine. He's in recovery.

267
00:16:18,590 --> 00:16:20,570
But we took a vial of C.S.F.
and tested it.

268
00:16:20,708 --> 00:16:21,160
Really?

269
00:16:21,583 --> 00:16:24,180
Turns out the bowing wasn't the cause
of his problems. It was a symptom.

270
00:16:24,378 --> 00:16:26,910
Oligoclonal bands
and increased intrathecal IGG.

271
00:16:27,006 --> 00:16:31,140
Which means multiple sclerosis. And the
reason it takes three of you to tell me this?

272
00:16:31,140 --> 00:16:33,490
Because we're having a disagreement
about whether or not it is M.S.

273
00:16:33,490 --> 00:16:34,610
No lesions on the M.R.I.

274
00:16:34,620 --> 00:16:36,600
It's early. He's
had the disease for maybe two weeks.

275
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:39,530
McDonald criteria requires six
months to make a definitive diagnosis.

276
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:41,130
Who cares about MacPhearson?

277
00:16:41,140 --> 00:16:43,070
- I hear he tortured kittens.
- McDonald.

278
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:45,500
Oh, McDonald.
Wonderful doctor, loved kittens.

279
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:47,550
The V.E.P. indicates slowing of the brain.

280
00:16:47,985 --> 00:16:49,290
Without the lesions,
we can't be sure.

281
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:51,770
Well, if it is, it's gone from
zero to 60 in three weeks,

282
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:54,120
which would indicate
rapidly progressive M.S.

283
00:16:54,408 --> 00:16:57,950
Not the fun M.S. with the balloons and the
bike rides for cripples in wheelchairs.

284
00:16:57,960 --> 00:17:00,539
- We should wait until...
- Start treating him now,

285
00:17:00,914 --> 00:17:04,043
maybe he can walk for another couple
of years, maybe live for another five.

286
00:17:05,070 --> 00:17:06,754
Break it to the family.
I'm going home.

287
00:17:07,540 --> 00:17:10,090
It'll take months
for a definitive diagnosis.

288
00:17:10,466 --> 00:17:11,633
What'll happen to me?

289
00:17:13,302 --> 00:17:16,170
M.S. is an incredibly variable disease.

290
00:17:16,180 --> 00:17:19,210
If it is M.S., and we're not
a hundred percent sure.

291
00:17:19,433 --> 00:17:20,700
What do you think is gonna happen?

292
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:27,210
There are some medications
to manage the symptoms,

293
00:17:27,220 --> 00:17:30,778
but as the disease progresses,
the problems will become more severe.

294
00:17:31,460 --> 00:17:33,360
Bowel and bladder dysfunction,

295
00:17:33,447 --> 00:17:35,650
loss of cognitive function, pain...

296
00:17:35,660 --> 00:17:36,742
It's gonna hurt?

297
00:17:39,270 --> 00:17:41,580
The brain's like a big jumble of wires.

298
00:17:41,770 --> 00:17:44,625
M.S. strips them of the insulation,
and the nerves die.

299
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:47,020
Brain interprets it as pain.

300
00:17:47,086 --> 00:17:50,339
But by starting treatment, we're gonna
prevent that for as long as possible.

301
00:17:51,380 --> 00:17:53,170
We're looking into
a couple of specialists,

302
00:17:53,180 --> 00:17:56,595
and until we get you squared away,
you'll stay here, okay?

303
00:18:17,574 --> 00:18:20,202
Security checked the videotapes
from all perimeter cameras.

304
00:18:20,202 --> 00:18:22,160
He's still gotta be in the hospital.
Where's Chase?

305
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:23,140
Main floor.

306
00:18:23,205 --> 00:18:25,310
Okay. You take the
cafeteria and administration.

307
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:27,520
I'll hit the research annex
and work my way back to you.

308
00:19:05,372 --> 00:19:05,914
Dan?

309
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:14,631
I'm not here. Leave a message.

310
00:19:20,721 --> 00:19:23,160
Dr. Cuddy. Great outfit.

311
00:19:23,557 --> 00:19:25,260
What are you doing
back here? Patient?

312
00:19:25,710 --> 00:19:29,438
No. Hooker. Went to my office
instead of my home.

313
00:19:39,907 --> 00:19:40,699
Dr. House.

314
00:19:42,190 --> 00:19:45,150
- Dan's missing.
- Yeah. I got that part from the message.

315
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:48,350
You said I was needed immediately. He
shouldn't move after a lumbar puncture.

316
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:50,720
I agree. He's gonna have
a very nasty headache.

317
00:19:51,130 --> 00:19:53,560
That would also be my opinion
if consulted tomorrow morning.

318
00:19:54,340 --> 00:19:57,000
We wanted to keep you informed.
He heard some pretty heavy news.

319
00:19:59,340 --> 00:20:01,890
This is not a toddler wandering
around a department store.

320
00:20:01,890 --> 00:20:04,420
He's 16. You'll find him.

321
00:20:05,380 --> 00:20:06,380
I'm going home.

322
00:20:07,851 --> 00:20:10,050
So when you say, "Call me if you
need anything", you mean don't call?

323
00:20:10,060 --> 00:20:12,272
No, I mean call me
if I could do something.

324
00:20:12,606 --> 00:20:14,130
I'm bad at search
parties, and I'm bad at

325
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:16,080
sitting around looking
nervous, doing nothing.

326
00:20:16,820 --> 00:20:18,695
What about his parents?
Should we call them?

327
00:20:18,862 --> 00:20:20,200
Why? Do you think
they're hiding him?

328
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:23,784
Make sure someone
checks the roof.

329
00:20:24,243 --> 00:20:27,360
Some of the orderlies keep the door
propped open so they can grab a smoke.

330
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:05,075
Dan. You okay?

331
00:21:12,499 --> 00:21:16,170
There are experimental treatments.
Ongoing research.

332
00:21:16,580 --> 00:21:18,714
Who knows what they'll discover
in a year or two.

333
00:21:18,980 --> 00:21:20,924
This is where I dropped the ball.

334
00:21:21,140 --> 00:21:23,343
Dan, we're standing
on the roof of the hospital.

335
00:21:26,054 --> 00:21:26,722
Dan.

336
00:21:28,060 --> 00:21:29,725
Dan, you're not on the field.

337
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:32,150
He doesn't know where he is.

338
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:33,520
- Dan.
- Foreman.

339
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:36,148
Dan.

340
00:21:38,358 --> 00:21:39,818
- Dan?
- Dan, no!

341
00:21:51,371 --> 00:21:52,331
Dr. Foreman.

342
00:21:54,750 --> 00:21:56,220
I assume you found the kid.

343
00:21:56,501 --> 00:21:58,040
He almost walked off the roof.

344
00:21:58,587 --> 00:21:59,320
Suicidal?

345
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:01,040
No, he thought he was
on his lacrosse field.

346
00:22:01,390 --> 00:22:03,590
Look, I was just gonna run
home, shower, change...

347
00:22:03,590 --> 00:22:05,385
Conscious? Yeah.

348
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:09,250
How'd you talk him down?
Actually, Chase tackled him.

349
00:22:09,260 --> 00:22:10,520
How come you didn't do it?

350
00:22:10,970 --> 00:22:13,685
Right. Well, I am black,
but he was closer.

351
00:22:16,730 --> 00:22:17,970
Come on.
You can ride up with me.

352
00:22:24,738 --> 00:22:26,670
Anybody tell the family
that their boy almost

353
00:22:26,670 --> 00:22:28,500
stepped off a roof?
They must be thrilled.

354
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:31,100
They're not suing, but I think
only because Chase asked them...

355
00:22:31,100 --> 00:22:33,420
Why does everybody
always think I'm being sarcastic?

356
00:22:33,430 --> 00:22:36,370
This is great news.
He doesn't have M.S.

357
00:22:36,458 --> 00:22:38,450
Parents should be thrilled. Well, the mom anyway.

358
00:22:38,660 --> 00:22:40,045
Of course, the dad probably doesn't know...

359
00:22:40,045 --> 00:22:41,671
Why doesn't he have M.S.?

360
00:22:41,671 --> 00:22:43,740
He was on the roof, thinking
he was on a lacrosse field.

361
00:22:43,740 --> 00:22:46,380
Conscious, and therefore not a
night terror. You want some of this?

362
00:22:46,843 --> 00:22:47,760
Yeah, sure.

363
00:22:48,180 --> 00:22:50,330
He was in an acute
confusional state,

364
00:22:50,340 --> 00:22:52,770
which doesn't fit with
a demyelinating disease like M.S.

365
00:22:52,780 --> 00:22:54,680
- Oligoclonal bands...
- Were real.

366
00:22:54,976 --> 00:22:58,540
They just mean something other than M.S.
So, what are they telling us?

367
00:22:58,814 --> 00:23:00,290
That the immune system is working?

368
00:23:00,357 --> 00:23:00,982
Right.

369
00:23:01,358 --> 00:23:02,930
He has an infection in his brain.

370
00:23:02,940 --> 00:23:04,160
What about sex?

371
00:23:04,736 --> 00:23:07,910
Well, it might get complicated.
I mean, we work together.

372
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:09,530
I'm older, certainly,
but maybe you like that.

373
00:23:09,540 --> 00:23:11,700
I meant maybe he
has neurosyphilis.

374
00:23:12,100 --> 00:23:14,590
- Nice cover.
- Sorry. R.P.R. was negative.

375
00:23:14,590 --> 00:23:16,550
We don't need a definitive
test to confirm this.

376
00:23:16,550 --> 00:23:18,330
Sure. Didn't need one to confirm M.S.

377
00:23:18,340 --> 00:23:20,830
Okay. Let's wait for you
to run titers on 1,400

378
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:22,950
viruses while this kid's
brain turns to mush.

379
00:23:22,960 --> 00:23:27,250
So the fact that he doesn't have M.S.,
it's really not good news after all.

380
00:23:27,260 --> 00:23:28,885
Well, it is if it's neurosyphilis.

381
00:23:29,136 --> 00:23:32,090
The likelihood of a false negative
on an R.P.R. test: 30%.

382
00:23:32,090 --> 00:23:35,770
Likelihood of a 16-year-old having sex:
roughly 120%.

383
00:23:35,851 --> 00:23:38,330
- I'll start him on I.V. penicillin.
- No, we're not gonna wait for that.

384
00:23:38,330 --> 00:23:41,350
The most effective way to deliver the drug
is right into his brain via the spine.

385
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:43,510
We can't.
In a cramped space like the brain,

386
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:45,570
increased intracranial
pressure from a high-volume

387
00:23:45,580 --> 00:23:47,470
drug like penicillin could
herniate his brain stem.

388
00:23:47,470 --> 00:23:50,620
It would kill him. No neurologist in his
right mind would recommend that.

389
00:23:50,824 --> 00:23:53,285
Show of hands. Who thinks
I'm not in my right mind?

390
00:23:54,453 --> 00:23:57,831
And who thinks I forget this
fairly basic neurological fact?

391
00:23:58,290 --> 00:24:00,250
Who thinks there's a third option?

392
00:24:02,210 --> 00:24:03,900
Very good. What's
the third choice?

393
00:24:04,045 --> 00:24:06,047
No idea. You just asked
if I thought there was one.

394
00:24:09,885 --> 00:24:12,970
Patient has a shunt in his brain.
There'll be no increased pressure.

395
00:24:12,980 --> 00:24:15,390
We can put as much penicillin
into his body as we want.

396
00:24:15,515 --> 00:24:18,185
Excellent. Inject him through
a lumbar puncture.

397
00:24:21,438 --> 00:24:24,630
One of us is gonna do this to you
twice a day for the next two weeks.

398
00:24:27,740 --> 00:24:30,270
- I'm ready. Go.
- He could get syphilis...

399
00:24:30,280 --> 00:24:31,865
even if he's not sexually active?

400
00:24:33,575 --> 00:24:37,204
Well, it's, it's unusual,
but it's possible.

401
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:39,956
Okay. Relax.

402
00:24:53,130 --> 00:24:56,470
It's infected,
with a really big hole,

403
00:24:56,470 --> 00:24:58,830
like you stuck a nail in it
to relieve the pressure.

404
00:24:58,840 --> 00:25:01,250
I wouldn't do that. Although
the wound is irregular.

405
00:25:01,260 --> 00:25:04,640
It's not cylindrical. It's shaped
like a triangle. So, not a nail.

406
00:25:05,565 --> 00:25:07,450
- Steak knife?
- Wife's nail file.

407
00:25:07,484 --> 00:25:08,450
Nail file.

408
00:25:09,720 --> 00:25:12,080
Yeah. Pain will make you
do stupid things.

409
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:15,992
- Something to take the edge off?
- Yeah.

410
00:25:18,578 --> 00:25:19,287
Cheers.

411
00:25:24,417 --> 00:25:26,500
So, you have family here
in Princeton?

412
00:25:27,330 --> 00:25:29,923
- No.
- Here on work?

413
00:25:30,060 --> 00:25:32,250
- No. Why are you...
- Does your penis hurt?

414
00:25:32,260 --> 00:25:34,469
No. What? Should it?

415
00:25:34,469 --> 00:25:37,960
No. Just thought I'd toss you
a really inappropriate question.

416
00:25:38,348 --> 00:25:39,620
Your lawyer's gonna love it.

417
00:25:39,620 --> 00:25:41,850
Why would I want to sue you?
I want you to treat me.

418
00:25:41,860 --> 00:25:44,280
- You're from Maplewood, New Jersey, right?
- Yeah.

419
00:25:44,521 --> 00:25:46,898
Now, why would you
drive 70 miles...

420
00:25:46,990 --> 00:25:50,318
to get treatment for a condition
that a nine-year-old could diagnose?

421
00:25:51,861 --> 00:25:54,560
It's the free-flowing pus
that's the tip-off.

422
00:25:54,560 --> 00:25:57,420
- I was in town.
- Not for family. Not for work.

423
00:25:57,620 --> 00:26:01,160
You drove 70 miles to a walk-in clinic.
You passed two hospitals on the road.

424
00:26:01,170 --> 00:26:03,390
Now, either you've got
a problem with those hospitals,

425
00:26:03,390 --> 00:26:04,590
or they have a problem with you.

426
00:26:04,590 --> 00:26:07,250
My guess is you've sued
half the doctors in Maplewood,

427
00:26:07,377 --> 00:26:09,462
and the rest are now
refusing to help you.

428
00:26:09,480 --> 00:26:13,280
It's ironic, isn't it?
Sort of like the boy who sued wolf.

429
00:26:13,758 --> 00:26:16,220
You know, I bet we have
a doctor here named Wolf.

430
00:26:16,220 --> 00:26:17,760
How perfect would that be?

431
00:26:18,790 --> 00:26:21,070
- I'm gonna page him.
- Okay. You know what? Thank you.

432
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:22,840
I'm gonna find a doctor
to take care of this.

433
00:26:23,700 --> 00:26:25,060
I didn't say I wouldn't treat you.

434
00:26:25,620 --> 00:26:28,200
We'll drain your knee, run
some lab work. Fix you right up.

435
00:26:28,210 --> 00:26:29,190
Why would you do that?

436
00:26:29,482 --> 00:26:30,692
I'm a people person.

437
00:26:32,110 --> 00:26:33,380
You actually treated him?

438
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:35,370
All I know is he sued some doctors.

439
00:26:35,380 --> 00:26:37,500
Who am I to assume they didn't
have it coming to them?

440
00:26:37,860 --> 00:26:39,830
The cutest little tennis outfit.

441
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:41,661
My God, I thought I
was gonna have a heart attack.

442
00:26:41,786 --> 00:26:43,790
Oh, my. I didn't see you
there. That is so embarrassing.

443
00:26:43,790 --> 00:26:44,956
How's your hooker doing?

444
00:26:45,140 --> 00:26:47,070
Sweet of you to ask.
Funny story.

445
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:48,670
She was gonna be hospital
administrator,

446
00:26:48,680 --> 00:26:50,960
but just hated having to
screw people like that.

447
00:26:50,970 --> 00:26:53,530
- I heard you found her on the roof.
- You have very acute hearing.

448
00:26:54,299 --> 00:26:55,230
You notify the parents?

449
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:56,510
In due course, of course.

450
00:26:56,551 --> 00:27:00,950
And is there a paternity bet
on the father of the patient?

451
00:27:00,960 --> 00:27:01,820
Doesn't sound like me.

452
00:27:01,820 --> 00:27:03,930
Well, it does,
actually, but doesn't mean you're guilty.

453
00:27:04,100 --> 00:27:06,394
- You think?
- I saw the parents in the lobby.

454
00:27:06,570 --> 00:27:08,050
Smart money's obviously
on the father.

455
00:27:09,064 --> 00:27:11,510
My guy knows a guy who can
get you in for 50 bucks.

456
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:15,320
Fine. Tell your guy, if I win, you attend
the faculty symposium, and you wear a tie.

457
00:27:15,445 --> 00:27:18,031
And if I win,
no clinic hours for a week.

458
00:27:18,740 --> 00:27:20,367
My guy will call your guy.

459
00:27:22,700 --> 00:27:24,412
She's very good at her job.

460
00:27:29,334 --> 00:27:31,200
The treatments should
start helping soon.

461
00:27:31,628 --> 00:27:35,006
Let us know if it gets easier to
focus on things, remember stuff.

462
00:27:36,883 --> 00:27:40,303
Hey, Dan. Isn't Dr. Cameron's
necklace a beauty?

463
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:42,472
Something South American, I think.

464
00:27:43,223 --> 00:27:44,660
Yeah. Guatemalan.

465
00:27:46,059 --> 00:27:47,435
It's a cool necklace.

466
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:52,065
- Thank you so much.
- The kid's in pain.

467
00:27:53,942 --> 00:27:55,950
Don't fight it. Just let it happen.

468
00:27:56,027 --> 00:27:56,778
No.

469
00:27:57,153 --> 00:27:58,250
- You 'll be dead in two days.
- No what?

470
00:27:58,260 --> 00:28:00,750
I give it a day. Dan? You okay?

471
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:01,440
Dan?

472
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:04,750
- Night terrors.
- Body decomposition once he's in the grave.

473
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:07,480
- Say good-bye to your mother and father.
- He's hearing voices.

474
00:28:07,490 --> 00:28:10,030
You're dying.
It's all over, Dan.

475
00:28:11,270 --> 00:28:14,421
You're dying. Dying. Dead!

