00:28:15,860 --> 00:28:18,270
Push two milligrams
I.V. Ativan, stat.

477
00:28:18,280 --> 00:28:21,553
- It's all over.
- Come on, Dan.

478
00:28:21,553 --> 00:28:23,170
Get out of my head!

479
00:28:26,030 --> 00:28:28,610
Auditory hallucination shows
further brain degeneration.

480
00:28:28,810 --> 00:28:32,850
Penicillin's not working. So either
it's a bad batch of penicillin,

481
00:28:32,860 --> 00:28:35,190
or our diagnosis is wrong.

482
00:28:36,620 --> 00:28:37,527
Square one.

483
00:28:38,862 --> 00:28:42,730
- Midnite.
- L.F.T.'s, B.U.N. and creatinine are all normal.

484
00:28:42,740 --> 00:28:45,270
- Diabetes is out, and no gap.
- There goes metabolic.

485
00:28:45,280 --> 00:28:48,000
- M.R.A. rules out vasculitis.
- "I" for inflammation.

486
00:28:48,010 --> 00:28:50,710
- Too young for anything degenerative.
- "D", see ya.

487
00:28:50,980 --> 00:28:53,460
"N" for neoplastic.
M.R.I. was clean.

488
00:28:54,740 --> 00:28:56,720
- "I" for inflammation.
- We already did that.

489
00:28:56,730 --> 00:28:59,180
Stupid to have two I's in one mnemonic.
What's the other one?

490
00:28:59,180 --> 00:28:59,841
Infection.

491
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:01,620
Oligoclonal bands still
have to mean something.

492
00:29:01,620 --> 00:29:04,300
But no fevers. White count's
elevated, but within range.

493
00:29:04,300 --> 00:29:07,130
We've tested for anything remotely
possible. Everything's negative.

494
00:29:07,140 --> 00:29:10,477
- C.T. scan rules out subdural.
- Trauma. Later much.

495
00:29:16,010 --> 00:29:20,140
You know the problem? "Midnight" is
actually spelled with a "G" and an "H".

496
00:29:21,321 --> 00:29:23,540
Just figure out
what those letters stand for.

497
00:29:27,952 --> 00:29:31,400
It's a sick brain, having fun,

498
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:35,627
torturing him, talking to him.

499
00:29:40,900 --> 00:29:42,440
Scaring the hell out of him.

500
00:29:45,261 --> 00:29:49,380
Get him an E.E.G., left and right E.O.G.,
esophageal microphones.

501
00:29:50,225 --> 00:29:53,895
If this thing wants to talk,
let's listen.

502
00:29:56,064 --> 00:29:59,820
We're missing something.
This is screwed-up.

503
00:30:00,068 --> 00:30:03,880
That's why you came up with
the brain talking to the virus thing?

504
00:30:03,988 --> 00:30:05,460
I panicked, okay?

505
00:30:06,140 --> 00:30:08,326
Sounded cool though.
They bought it.

506
00:30:11,900 --> 00:30:13,414
Oh, crap.

507
00:30:14,340 --> 00:30:16,180
Another reason I don't like
meeting patients.

508
00:30:16,180 --> 00:30:18,378
If they don't know what you look like,
they can't yell at you.

509
00:30:19,295 --> 00:30:20,171
Here we go.

510
00:30:25,426 --> 00:30:27,178
How can you just sit there?

511
00:30:28,638 --> 00:30:30,140
If I eat standing up, I spill.

512
00:30:30,140 --> 00:30:33,393
Our son is dying,
and you could care less.

513
00:30:34,310 --> 00:30:37,272
We're going through hell.
You're doing nothing?

514
00:30:38,523 --> 00:30:40,570
I'm sorry. You need to vent.
I understand.

515
00:30:40,580 --> 00:30:42,250
Don't be condescending.

516
00:30:43,236 --> 00:30:45,029
You haven't checked
in on him once.

517
00:30:45,989 --> 00:30:48,100
Blood pressure is 110 over 70.

518
00:30:48,825 --> 00:30:51,400
His shunt is patent, well-placed
in the right lateral ventricle.

519
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:53,890
The E.K.G. shows a normal Q.R.S.
with deep-wave

520
00:30:53,900 --> 00:30:56,230
inversions throughout both
limb and precordial leads.

521
00:30:56,240 --> 00:30:58,877
L.F.T.'s are elevated,
but only twice the normal range.

522
00:30:58,980 --> 00:31:01,629
Oh, yeah. And he's hearing voices.

523
00:31:06,660 --> 00:31:07,850
Go hold his hand.

524
00:31:10,380 --> 00:31:12,098
Go on. I'll bus your tray.

525
00:31:26,112 --> 00:31:29,115
- Got any sample bags on you?
- I don't believe you.

526
00:31:29,449 --> 00:31:32,710
- You're gonna run D.N.A. tests?
- Their son is deathly ill.

527
00:31:32,720 --> 00:31:35,050
I know. It's terrible.
But the fact is,

528
00:31:35,060 --> 00:31:37,250
if I don't keep busy with
trivial things like this,

529
00:31:37,260 --> 00:31:39,320
- I'm afraid I might start to cry.
- You're an ass.

530
00:31:39,740 --> 00:31:42,045
Yeah? You want to double the bet?

531
00:31:53,181 --> 00:31:55,391
General Hospital is on channel 6.

532
00:31:55,780 --> 00:31:58,853
Dan's brain's not showing
channel 6 right now. Only mush.

533
00:31:59,228 --> 00:32:00,855
No epileptiform activity.

534
00:32:03,080 --> 00:32:05,840
- What are you doing?
- Waiting for C.B.C. and CHEM-7.

535
00:32:05,985 --> 00:32:08,154
Good. Run D.N.A. on these.

536
00:32:10,782 --> 00:32:12,825
- What's this?
- Parents' coffee cups.

537
00:32:14,744 --> 00:32:17,140
- I can't believe you.
- I've had this conversation once already.

538
00:32:17,246 --> 00:32:19,415
If you've got something else to do, do it.
Otherwise, do this.

539
00:32:28,299 --> 00:32:31,344
- Dr. House.
- Hey. Mr. Funsten.

540
00:32:31,410 --> 00:32:34,013
I was wondering when you'd be back.
You got some papers for me?

541
00:32:34,681 --> 00:32:36,790
You've caused me
considerable mental distress.

542
00:32:36,790 --> 00:32:38,184
I certainly hope so.

543
00:32:39,120 --> 00:32:41,020
What? Too cheap to get
your lawyer to serve

544
00:32:41,020 --> 00:32:42,850
it for you, or is it
just more fun this way?

545
00:32:42,860 --> 00:32:44,941
I'm obviously prepared
to consider a settlement.

546
00:32:45,420 --> 00:32:46,693
You have gonorrhea.

547
00:32:49,612 --> 00:32:50,571
No, I don't.

548
00:32:50,738 --> 00:32:53,282
Well, maybe you're right,
but I have the lab result says you do.

549
00:32:53,500 --> 00:32:56,100
Could be a false positive,
and normally I'd run a second test,

550
00:32:56,100 --> 00:32:58,870
- ...but since you're here, I'll just go with the first.
- You're just trying to scare me.

551
00:32:58,880 --> 00:33:00,990
It's reportable,
you know. Public health issue.

552
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:02,542
Well, I'll be sure to let my wife know.

553
00:33:02,870 --> 00:33:05,070
Don't bother yourself.
The state will call for you.

554
00:33:05,169 --> 00:33:08,130
Look, if you're clean, I'm sure
it'll all blow over. No big deal.

555
00:33:08,140 --> 00:33:11,220
There's an easy way to find out.
Get one of your doctors to run a test.

556
00:33:15,304 --> 00:33:18,391
These are mine now.
I'll see you in court.

557
00:33:22,311 --> 00:33:24,720
West Nile negative. Not
surprising since not too

558
00:33:24,720 --> 00:33:26,830
many mosquitoes passing
through Jersey in December.

559
00:33:26,840 --> 00:33:29,470
- No eastern equine encephalitis.
- You guys aren't gonna believe this.

560
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:30,028
What's that?

561
00:33:30,570 --> 00:33:32,739
House is right.
The father's not the father.

562
00:33:34,380 --> 00:33:35,700
Dude doubled up on me.

563
00:33:37,201 --> 00:33:38,536
You're not gonna believe this.

564
00:33:39,020 --> 00:33:40,455
The mother's not the mother either.

565
00:33:43,541 --> 00:33:46,220
It's not a good idea
to move your son in his condition.

566
00:33:46,377 --> 00:33:48,810
- We just want a second opinion.
- We need an answer.

567
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:53,134
You idiots. You lied to me.

568
00:33:53,160 --> 00:33:54,480
We didn't lie about anything.

569
00:33:55,060 --> 00:33:57,597
You, on the other hand, accused
us of molesting our son.

570
00:33:57,920 --> 00:33:58,540
Perfect.

571
00:33:58,540 --> 00:34:01,142
Can we get off my screw ups
and focus on theirs?

572
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:03,800
Theirs is bigger.
You're not Dan's parents.

573
00:34:03,895 --> 00:34:04,740
We're his parents.

574
00:34:04,812 --> 00:34:06,630
He was adopted. He doesn't need to know.

575
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:09,050
- I do.
- Adoption makes us just as much...

576
00:34:09,060 --> 00:34:13,029
Listen. When we were taking
his medical history, were you confused?

577
00:34:13,404 --> 00:34:15,630
Did you think we were looking for
a genetic clue to his condition,

578
00:34:15,640 --> 00:34:17,430
or did you think we were
trying to ascertain who

579
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:19,786
loves him the most in
the whole wide world?

580
00:34:19,870 --> 00:34:21,287
How did you find out about this?

581
00:34:22,740 --> 00:34:25,930
- I sampled their D.N.A.
- We didn't give you any D.N.A.

582
00:34:25,940 --> 00:34:27,710
Your coffee cups from the cafeteria.

583
00:34:27,919 --> 00:34:29,440
You can't do that.

584
00:34:29,440 --> 00:34:32,020
Again, why are we getting
hung up on what I did?

585
00:34:32,030 --> 00:34:33,610
Your medical history is useless.

586
00:34:33,620 --> 00:34:37,660
No. We gave you a detailed
history of his biological mother.

587
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:41,099
Her history.
Non-smoker, good health,

588
00:34:41,250 --> 00:34:43,910
low cholesterol,
no blood pressure problems.

589
00:34:44,018 --> 00:34:46,030
Dan was adopted two weeks
after he was born.

590
00:34:46,030 --> 00:34:48,590
You have his history. There's nothing
you need to know that we didn't tell you.

591
00:34:48,590 --> 00:34:49,524
Sounds reasonable.

592
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:54,110
Well, if you want to transfer
your boy, that is your choice.

593
00:34:54,120 --> 00:34:56,656
- I still think it's the wrong...
- Was she vaccinated?

594
00:34:58,533 --> 00:35:01,470
The biological mother. When she was a
baby, did she get her vaccinations?

595
00:35:01,480 --> 00:35:04,040
Dan was vaccinated.
At six months.

596
00:35:05,660 --> 00:35:08,543
Do you know why kids
get vaccinated at six months?

597
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:10,870
Because before that
they are protected...

598
00:35:10,880 --> 00:35:13,464
by their biological mother's
immune system.

599
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:16,259
So, was she vaccinated?

600
00:35:20,040 --> 00:35:23,000
An infant picks up
a regular old measles virus.

601
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:24,517
Gets a rash.

602
00:35:24,690 --> 00:35:28,690
He's extremely uncomfortable,
has a wicked fever, but he lives.

603
00:35:28,690 --> 00:35:32,340
Here's the kicker.
Once every million or so times,

604
00:35:32,608 --> 00:35:33,980
the virus mutates.

605
00:35:34,861 --> 00:35:37,196
Instead of Dan having
a fever and a rash,

606
00:35:37,488 --> 00:35:39,991
the virus travels
to his brain and hides,

607
00:35:40,491 --> 00:35:41,660
like a time bomb.

608
00:35:42,201 --> 00:35:45,037
In this case, for 16 years.

609
00:35:45,080 --> 00:35:47,620
Subacute sclerosing panencephalitis.

610
00:35:48,499 --> 00:35:52,250
I know. There's only been 20 cases in
the United States in the last 30 years.

611
00:35:52,260 --> 00:35:54,839
I suppose you could make
an argument the kid's still in stage I.

612
00:35:55,590 --> 00:35:57,610
Once S.S.P.E. moves
to stage II, it's...

613
00:35:57,620 --> 00:36:00,386
Boom. Stage II is universally fatal.

614
00:36:01,053 --> 00:36:03,620
I assume its impossible to know
when he might move into stage II.

615
00:36:03,620 --> 00:36:07,643
He's already started showing symptoms.
Could be a month. Could be tonight.

616
00:36:08,519 --> 00:36:10,470
Can we treat it?
Ask the neurologist.

617
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:12,231
Intraventricular interferon.

618
00:36:12,773 --> 00:36:14,590
Not gonna shove a spike
into his brain and drip

619
00:36:14,590 --> 00:36:16,770
interferon without
confirming this diagnosis.

620
00:36:17,020 --> 00:36:17,653
Tap him.

621
00:36:17,778 --> 00:36:20,730
We won't get a reliable result for
measles antibodies in his C.S.F.

622
00:36:20,740 --> 00:36:22,020
Not after everything
we've given him.

623
00:36:22,020 --> 00:36:25,250
So the wrong treatment kills
any hope of the right diagnosis.

624
00:36:25,260 --> 00:36:26,913
Why do people lie to me?

625
00:36:29,220 --> 00:36:30,541
Could also kill him.

626
00:36:30,875 --> 00:36:34,503
Your ball, Foreman. Tell me I
don't have to biopsy his brain.

627
00:36:36,214 --> 00:36:38,382
Well, there is one other way.

628
00:36:40,051 --> 00:36:41,510
You sure this isn't gonna hurt?

629
00:36:41,928 --> 00:36:44,096
Yeah. It's just scary as hell.

630
00:36:44,420 --> 00:36:45,940
See, we go through the pupil.

631
00:36:46,224 --> 00:36:48,726
But you won't feel it.
The eye's been paralyzed.

632
00:36:48,726 --> 00:36:50,561
The needle travels
to the back of the eye,

633
00:36:50,561 --> 00:36:53,105
which is where we'll perform
the biopsy on your retina.

634
00:36:59,190 --> 00:37:02,320
So we've confirmed that
the problem is this mutated virus.

635
00:37:02,490 --> 00:37:05,960
The treatment for S.S.P.E.
is intraventricular interferon.

636
00:37:06,035 --> 00:37:08,660
We implant an ommaya reservoir
under the scalp,

637
00:37:09,038 --> 00:37:10,880
which is connected to
a ventricular catheter...

638
00:37:10,880 --> 00:37:13,920
that delivers the antiviral
directly to the left hemisphere.

639
00:37:13,930 --> 00:37:17,170
You want us to consent to this? I don't
even understand what you're talking about.

640
00:37:17,460 --> 00:37:19,257
Well, the antiviral...

641
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:23,844
Look. I'm sorry.

642
00:37:24,650 --> 00:37:27,580
I can explain this as best
I can, but the notion that

643
00:37:27,580 --> 00:37:29,700
you're gonna fully understand
your son's treatment...

644
00:37:29,700 --> 00:37:33,000
and make an informed decision is...
is kind of insane.

645
00:37:35,300 --> 00:37:36,524
Here's what you need to know.

646
00:37:38,230 --> 00:37:39,193
It's dangerous.

647
00:37:40,100 --> 00:37:41,028
It could kill him.

648
00:37:42,770 --> 00:37:43,781
You should do it.

649
00:37:55,850 --> 00:37:56,970
Did you need something else?

650
00:38:16,772 --> 00:38:20,050
You can't order a $3,200
D.N.A. test to win a bet.

651
00:38:20,060 --> 00:38:21,777
It's not an actual cost.

652
00:38:22,480 --> 00:38:26,070
I don't know if you know this, but the
hospital actually owns the sequencing machine.

653
00:38:26,080 --> 00:38:26,615
I'm serious.

654
00:38:26,615 --> 00:38:28,850
Well. Tell the parents to submit
the bill to insurance.

655
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:30,980
Insurance is not gonna
pay for a bet.

656
00:38:30,980 --> 00:38:34,140
Should. We don't make that bet,
the kid dies.

657
00:38:34,890 --> 00:38:37,400
Not for the paternity bet,
I never would have taken their D.N.A.

658
00:38:37,400 --> 00:38:38,960
Without their D.N.A., we
never would have discovered

659
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:41,339
that Dan was adopted, which
was the key to this case.

660
00:38:42,965 --> 00:38:44,884
You just don't want to pay your end.

661
00:38:45,760 --> 00:38:48,230
Big mistake. My guy knows a guy.

662
00:38:48,346 --> 00:38:51,390
Fine. I will let you out of
clinic duty for one week,

663
00:38:51,557 --> 00:38:54,852
after you pay the 3,200
for the P.C.R. test.

664
00:39:04,320 --> 00:39:06,906
Well, now, there's
the hundred you owe me.

665
00:39:08,407 --> 00:39:10,284
Here's a hundred
I won from Cameron.

666
00:39:10,493 --> 00:39:13,204
200 I took off of Foreman.

667
00:39:14,430 --> 00:39:16,999
And 600...

668
00:39:17,100 --> 00:39:18,250
I got from Wilson.

669
00:39:20,900 --> 00:39:21,796
Very bitter.

670
00:39:25,980 --> 00:39:27,280
Hey. Good morning.

671
00:39:28,260 --> 00:39:30,679
Good news on your E.E.G.
Treatment is working.

672
00:39:31,010 --> 00:39:33,015
And your immune system is responding.

673
00:39:33,766 --> 00:39:36,580
I know it's early,
but I just want to take a look.

674
00:39:38,354 --> 00:39:41,482
Alright. Let's see what
that brain of yours can do.

675
00:39:41,982 --> 00:39:45,319
Name as many animals as you can
that start with the letter "O".

676
00:39:46,237 --> 00:39:47,321
Ostrich.

677
00:39:48,489 --> 00:39:51,130
Ox. Old elephant.

678
00:39:51,820 --> 00:39:53,619
Well, that's two better
than last time.

679
00:39:54,870 --> 00:39:56,705
How you doing with
the whole adoption thing?

680
00:39:57,581 --> 00:40:00,500
- I knew since fifth grade.
